args: Someone is here to see you,\n{player_name}.
Oh? I'd better go see them, then.
Er, should it happen to be someone from\nthe orchestra, please do not tell them\nthat I am here.
Don't worry, I won't betray your\nwhereabouts to anyone.
I am sorry to ask this of you.
Can I help you? ...Oh, you're that friend\nof Lucretia's, from—
Do not play coy, sir—I know she is here.
Ever since her sudden disappearance,\nI have been looking high and low for her.
This is the last place I have to check.
Look, I understand that you're worried,\nbut she's—
Well, if she's not here, you won't mind me\ncoming in and looking around.
Vixel? Whatever are you doing here?!
I'm sorry, Lucretia. I tried to stop him.
You have nothing to apologize for.\nNow just what is going on here, Lucretia?
Canceling all of your upcoming recitals\nand disappearing doesn't sound like you.
You've caused a great deal of trouble for\nthe orchestra you were scheduled to be\nperforming with. What were you thinking?!
I'm done singing on the stage.
After how much you used to love singing,\nyou're just going to walk away?!
It's BECAUSE I love singing that I quit!\nBut this conversation is pointless; there's\nnothing you can say to change my mind.
Let's just take it easy here, you two.
...Lucretia, I'm not here on behalf of the\norchestra. I'm here to help you.
I know how much music means to you.
As a fellow musician—as well as your\nfriendly rival—let me give you a warning:
The world of music isn't one where\nyou can come and go as you please.\nI should know...
But I'm not just ＂the songstress.＂\nI am Lucretia!
Do you mind if I try talking to her, Vixel?
The words of someone who has nothing to\ndo with music might actually have a better\nchance of reaching her right now.
Whatever she does, please make sure she\nshe has no regrets.
This is the right thing to do, right...?\nYes, of course. It's clearly the only option.
I apologize for rushing out as I did.
Can you tell me what you meant by what\nyou said earlier?
That part about not being the songstress.
Is that perhaps the real reason you're\nturning your back on singing?

*sigh* I suppose there's no point in trying
to hide it anymore. I didn't want to say
anything because I feared it would spoil
your image of me, but—
You are kind to say so.
As you know, people always refer to me as\nthe ＂songstress of the century.＂
But every time they call me that, I feel it's\nthe only thing I am ever allowed to be.\nAnd that...scares me.

All this time, I've tried to be what the
world wants from me—from how I sing
on stage to how I behave once I'm off it.
All so I don't betray anyone's expectations.
That's right. There's no space for any ＂me＂\nother than the one other people want.
The woman singing is not Lucretia.\nShe is merely an anonymous songstress.
At this rate, I fear singing will become\nthe ONLY thing that defines me, and\neverything else will simply...disappear.
So that was why you gave it up?
Yes. I feel like the only way to stay sane\nis to make sure I am more than that.
Because as it stands, if you take singing\nfrom me... Well, there's nothing left.
But do you really think it's true that\nsinging alone defines you?
Oh, you're an incredible singer.\nThere's no denying that.
But after living with you for a while,\nI've also learned more about you.

Like your housework skills, for example.
I don't know many people who could set a
kitchen on fire AND somehow manage to
soak the entire floor of a castle.
I can't. Because it's another part of what\nmakes you who you are.
I do. There's also the fact you're strong in\nbattle, that you're confident in your\ndecisions, and that you're a little fragile.
Those are all things that define you—\nthere's far more to the Lucretia I know\nthan just singing.
So the idea you're nothing but a songstress\nis simply not true.
We think the other facets of you are just as\ncharming as your singing, too—probably\nmore than anyone else would.
So don't be so scared to show the world\nwho you really are. Don't you think you\nshould live your life the way you want to?
You really think it's okay for me to not lie\nabout who I am?
Of course. You should just be you.
Then I will do just that! I'll return to\nsinging and be who I want to be!
All of you know me better than anyone,\nso if you believe in me, so can I!
